\ell_{p}
1\leqslant p<\infty
\left(x_{n}\right)_{n=1}^{\infty}
\left(y_{n}\right)_{n=1}^{\infty}
{\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left|x_{n}\right|^{p}}
{\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left|y_{n}\right|^{p}}
\alpha,\beta\in\mathbb{R}
\left[\alpha\left(x_{n}\right)_{n=1}^{\infty}+\beta\left(y_{n}\right)_{n=1}^{\infty}\right]\in\ell_{p}
{\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\left|\alpha x_{n}+\beta y_{n}\right|^{p}}<\infty
